<div class="quotetitle">blargg wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />If you delay frames by the repeating pattern 16, 17, 17, 16, 17, 17 ...  then the average is exactly 16.666666... msec between frames. Moral of the story: regardless of timing granularity, you can <em>on average</em> get a delay to any precision you like. You could have the average delay be exactly 16.1234567 msec, even though you can only delay by whole milliseconds.<br /></div><br /><br />It worked for Allegro. Well, now I get exactly 60FPS, thanks a lot, since it was a very very old issue.<br /><br />About the sound, I'm still having problems with sync... but I'm thinking &amp; trying different things...<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=39">Zepper</a> — Wed Jan 16, 2008 7:53 am</p><hr />
