<div class="quotetitle">Fx3 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />- If not wrong, Allegro's <em>rest(15)</em> takes <strong>much more time</strong> than 15/1000 of a second when executed sequentially. :D WTF?<br /></div><br />Usually a delay routine only guarantees that <em>at least</em> the specified amount of time passes, <em>not</em> that no more than that will pass. Thus, delays aren't useful for long-term timing, just as an a more friendly alternative to a loop that constantly waits until enough time has passed (by reading the current time repeatedly). As long as you have a readable timer that has a resolution of 1/60 second, or several times that, you should be fine.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=17">blargg</a> — Tue Jan 01, 2008 10:55 pm</p><hr />
