<author><name><![CDATA[blargg]]></name></author>
<updated>2007-12-30T20:34:21-07:00</updated>
<published>2007-12-30T20:34:21-07:00</published>
<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=3808&amp;p=29952#p29952</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=3808&amp;p=29952#p29952"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[The NESticle high-pitched sound]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=3808&amp;p=29952#p29952"><![CDATA[
If you delay frames by the repeating pattern 16, 17, 17, 16, 17, 17 ...  then the average is exactly 16.666666... msec between frames. Moral of the story: regardless of timing granularity, you can <em>on average</em> get a delay to any precision you like. You could have the average delay be exactly 16.1234567 msec, even though you can only delay by whole milliseconds.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=17">blargg</a> — Sun Dec 30, 2007 8:34 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
